Veteran Fuji musicians, Remi Aluko and Wale Thompson, alongside other entertainers, are set to thrill spectators at the three-day Eid-el-Fitri show tagged ‘Itunu Awe Bumper Show’, running from today, Friday, April 29 to May 6, 2022, in Lagos. The event, organised by The Studio By Troy, to celebrate the Islamic festivity after the 30-day Ramadan fasting, would be a conglomeration of multiple shows featuring various entertainment activities.The organiser of the event and Chief Executive Officer of The Studio By Troy, Sola Fajobi, is an award-winning entertainment entrepreneur who had organised reality TV shows, such as, ‘The Next Movie Star’ and ‘Super Mum,’ amongst others. The headliners of the event Juju musician and the ‘Lalale Friday’ crooner, Wale Thompson was billed to perform on Tuesday, May 3, while Remi Aluko would perform at the closing of the event, on Friday, May 6. Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com